Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell[TextData[{
 
 CounterBox["Section"],
 StyleBox[" | ", "SectionBar"],
 "Quantum coherence and correlation functions"
}], "Section",
 CounterAssignments->{{"Section", 4}},
 CellID->46234106,ExpressionUUID->"a2324337-381a-e245-8136-aa987057e6de"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["This chapter introduces the concept of coherence \
functions by first establishing a classical framework before transitioning to \
a quantum mechanical description of an atom interacting with an \
electromagnetic field. Proceeding to define first-order correlation and \
coherence, subsequently extending these principles to second-order coherence. \
We explore how, in the context of a single field, second-order coherence \
relates directly to photon statistics of quantum states of light", \
"Abstract"]], "Text",
 CellID->102457537,ExpressionUUID->"f2009e48-071a-2142-a4c1-5f922ea2ad32"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Classical coherence functions", "Subsection",
 CellID->478270874,ExpressionUUID->"e7de361d-dd46-6a49-9db2-d0b7a5c22668"],

Cell["Consider the Young\[CloseCurlyQuote]s two slit experiment setup", "Text",
 CellID->230818498,ExpressionUUID->"a4bbff76-eab6-0043-b57c-bbfee65ac0dc"],

